-- India's Maruti up on plan to seek minority shareholder nod for Gujarat plant
-- By Abhishek Vishnoi
-- Mon Mar 17, 2014 11:43PM EDT
-- None



MUMBAI, March 18 (Reuters) - Shares of Maruti Suzuki India <MRTI.NS> surged 9.3 percent in pre-open trading on plans to seek minority shareholder approval to set up a plant in Gujarat as a unit of Suzuki Motor Corp <7269.T>, after the proposed move drew opposition from the company's leading institutional investors.

